ddressing the need for a fluid and responsive approach to the study of visual meaning-making, this book relies on multiple methodologies such as semiotics, research-creation, multimodal discourse analysis, ethnography and phenomenology and shows how each method has something to offer toward the understanding of the social and cultural work of images in our globally oriented cultures"--cProvided by publisher.  a4310aGuevara, Che,d1928-1967vPortraits.10aKorda, Alberto,d1928-2001.tGuerillero her√≥ico.10aGuevara, Che,d1928-1967xInfluence. 0aGuerrillaszLatin AmericavPortraits. 0aPortraitsxPolitical aspects. 0aPortraitsxSocial aspects. 0aPhotographsxPolitical aspects. 0aPhotographsxSocial aspects. 0aVisual communication. 0aSemiotics. 0aBloomsbury advances in semiotics.423Cover imageuhttp://www.netread.com/jcusers2/bk1388/231/9781472505231/image/lgcover.9781472505231.jpg  aF 2849.22 G85 C28114 2015c1hUAHS-Bi0162035232022  aF 2849.22 G85 C28114 2015wLCc1i0162035232022d1/16/2017e1/3/2017lON_SHELFmUAHSSn7p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu2/11/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79018345bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/31991306